        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 29 at 7:09PM MDT by NWS Missoula MT</headline>
        <description>At 706 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking an intense snow shower 7
miles southeast of Divide, or 19 miles south of Butte, moving north
at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Visibility one-half mile or less.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Intense snowfall rates will lead to winter driving
conditions on I-15 and I-90 with periods of low visibility.

This includes Interstate 90 between mile markers 230 and 231.
</description>
        <instruction>This storm may intensify, so be certain to monitor local radio
stations and available television stations for additional information
and possible warnings from the National Weather Service.</instruction>
